1528
02:33:32,560 --> 02:33:37,840
Returning to Pelagia, he held her face 
in his hands and then embraced her.

1529
02:33:39,439 --> 02:33:44,080
When the light flashed three times from 
the sea and Warren returned the signal,  

1530
02:33:44,720 --> 02:33:51,040
Corelli shook his hand, kissed his father-in-law 
on both cheeks and went to Pelagia once more.  

1531
02:33:52,240 --> 02:33:57,599
There was nothing to be said. He knew 
that her mouth was trembling with grief  

1532
02:33:57,600 --> 02:34:04,880
and his throat was tight with the same emotion. 
He stroked her cheek tenderly and kissed her eyes.  

1533
02:34:06,080 --> 02:34:10,559
He heard the sound of the boat approaching 
and looked up to see the shadows of two men  

1534
02:34:10,560 --> 02:34:17,760
inside it. The four approached the boat and the 
doctor said, 'Go well, Antonio, and return.'

1535
02:34:19,280 --> 02:34:24,719
'May God hear you,' said the captain, 
and for the last time he held Pelagia.

1536
02:34:26,560 --> 02:34:30,800
After he had climbed into the boat, 
disappearing into the darkness like a ghost,  

1537
02:34:31,520 --> 02:34:37,360
Pelagia ran into the waves until the sea reached 
her thighs, but though she tried to catch sight of  

1538
02:34:37,359 --> 02:34:45,759
him, she saw nothing. A terrible emptiness seized 
her and she put her hands to her face and wept,  

1539
02:34:46,319 --> 02:34:52,479
bent over in pain, her cries carried off in the 
wind and were lost in the sound of the sea.
 
 
 

