1541
02:34:57,760 --> 02:35:02,080
1943-9: The Years of Terror

1542
02:35:04,080 --> 02:35:07,040
Of the German occupation there is little to say,  

1543
02:35:07,840 --> 02:35:13,040
except that it caused the islanders to feel more 
appreciation for the Italians they had lost.  

1544
02:35:14,080 --> 02:35:18,399
It seldom happens that a people can learn 
to feel friendly towards their oppressors,  

1545
02:35:19,120 --> 02:35:23,840
but hardly since Roman times had there 
been any other kind of rule in Cephallonia.  

1546
02:35:24,800 --> 02:35:30,240
Now there were no more Italians working in the 
fields beside the farmers in order to escape the  

1547
02:35:30,240 --> 02:35:36,559
boredom of army life, there were no more football 
matches between teams that quarrelled and cheated,  

1548
02:35:37,280 --> 02:35:42,000
there were no flirtations with girls by 
soldiers who had a cigarette hanging from  

1549
02:35:42,000 --> 02:35:48,000
the corners of their mouths. There were no 
more voices sending out opera tunes across  

1550
02:35:48,000 --> 02:35:54,000
the pine trees of the mountains. Gone were 
the charming chicken-thieves, and in their  

1551
02:35:54,000 --> 02:36:00,479
place came a period of time that the doctor 
recorded in his History as the worst time of all.

1552
02:36:01,920 --> 02:36:08,399
The islanders remember that the Germans were 
not human beings. They were machines without  

1553
02:36:08,399 --> 02:36:16,000
principles, machines that only knew how to loot 
and kill, without any passion except the love of  

1554
02:36:16,000 --> 02:36:22,240
strength, and without belief except in their 
natural right to destroy an inferior race.

1555
02:36:23,520 --> 02:36:30,320
The Italians had of course been thieves, but their 
shame when caught showed that they recognized  

1556
02:36:30,319 --> 02:36:36,639
their guilt. The Germans came into the house 
at any time of day, kicked over the furniture,  

1557
02:36:37,200 --> 02:36:43,439
beat the occupants, however old or young, and 
in front of their eyes carried away whatever  

1558
02:36:43,439 --> 02:36:49,280
they liked. Both Pelagia and her father were 
beaten at different times for no apparent  

1559
02:36:49,280 --> 02:36:56,960
cause. Drosoula had cigarettes burned into her 
skin for frowning at an officer. The doctor had  

1560
02:36:56,960 --> 02:37:02,720
all his precious medical equipment, gathered 
together over twenty years of poverty, broken  

1561
02:37:02,720 --> 02:37:08,800
in his presence by four officers whose hearts 
were as dark and empty as the caves of hell.

1562
02:37:10,319 --> 02:37:14,880
When in November 1944 the German 
troops were ordered to withdraw,  

1563
02:37:15,520 --> 02:37:18,560
they destroyed every building 
for which they found the time,  

1564
02:37:19,120 --> 02:37:24,479
and the inhabitants of Cephallonia rose up against 
them and fought them all the way to the sea.

1565
02:37:26,479 --> 02:37:32,639
But the night before he left, Gunter Weber, who 
had ashamedly stayed away from the house since the  

1566
02:37:32,640 --> 02:37:38,720
time of the killings, brought his record player 
and his collection of Marlene Dietrich records  

1567
02:37:38,720 --> 02:37:43,440
and left them outside Pelagia's door, 
as he had promised in happier days.  

1568
02:37:44,720 --> 02:37:50,241
He wrote a note in Italian: 'God be 
with you, I will remember you always.'

1569
02:37:52,000 --> 02:37:58,880
Pelagia hid the record player in the hole in the 
floor, with Antonio's mandolin and Carlo's papers,  

1570
02:37:59,600 --> 02:38:02,241
and it survived the terrible years that followed.

