Is this what I've been fighting for, you cow?'

1658
02:47:18,479 --> 02:47:23,439
Pelagia stood up, her lips trembling, 
and said, 'Mandras, let me out.'

1659
02:47:24,399 --> 02:47:29,439
'Let me out,' he repeated, 'let me out. 
Poor little thing's frightened, is she?'  

1660
02:47:30,240 --> 02:47:35,519
He came up to her and struck her across the 
face so hard that she spun round before she  

1661
02:47:35,520 --> 02:47:41,680
fell. He kicked her in the stomach and bent down 
to pick her up by the wrists, then he threw her  

1662
02:47:41,680 --> 02:47:47,840
on the bed and, quite against his original 
intentions, began to tear at her clothes.

1663
02:47:48,479 --> 02:47:54,240
This rape of women was something that he could 
not help, it seemed. It was a feeling that came  

1664
02:47:54,240 --> 02:48:00,319
from deep inside him, something he had learned 
in years of not needing to explain his actions to  

1665
02:48:00,319 --> 02:48:08,000
anyone. It was his natural right, and the violence 
was much more exciting than the sexual act itself.

1666
02:48:09,200 --> 02:48:16,800
But Pelagia fought. Her nails broke in his flesh, 
she struck him with hands and knees and elbows,  

1667
02:48:16,800 --> 02:48:23,520
she screamed and struggled. To Mandras her 
resistance was unreasonable, he was failing  

1668
02:48:23,520 --> 02:48:30,400
despite his weight and strength, and he sat back 
and hit her repeatedly. Then suddenly he tried to  

1669
02:48:30,399 --> 02:48:36,960
pull up her skirts. The solid weight of her gun 
fell out of its pocket and landed beside her head  

1670
02:48:36,960 --> 02:48:42,800
on the pillow, but Mandras did not see it, and 
when the bullet cracked through his shoulder,  

1671
02:48:42,800 --> 02:48:48,400
the shock knocked him backwards and he 
gazed at Pelagia in shock and accusation.

1672
02:48:49,840 --> 02:48:54,400
Drosoula heard the crack of the gunshot 
just as she came through the kitchen door  

1673
02:48:54,399 --> 02:49:00,319
and at first she did not recognize the sound, 
but then she knew what it was and took the  

1674
02:49:00,319 --> 02:49:06,160
Italian gun from the drawer. Without thinking, 
knowing that thought would make her a coward,  

1675
02:49:06,720 --> 02:49:11,840
she pushed open the door of Pelagia's 
room and saw there the unthinkable.

1676
02:49:12,960 --> 02:49:17,760
She had thought that Pelagia might have 
shot herself, that there might be thieves,  

1677
02:49:17,760 --> 02:49:23,360
but when she burst in, she saw the doctor's 
daughter leaning up on her elbow, her face  

1678
02:49:23,359 --> 02:49:31,519
swollen and bloody, her lips split, her clothes 
